<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<!--Below;We can also change the styles in a paragraph/heading texts using Javascript-->
   <title> Changing Texts styles using JS </title>
</head>
<body>
<!--Below;This is a paragraph,it has an ID 'jstyle' and the default style is set to gold-->
   <p id="jstyle" style="color: gold;">What is my color RN? </p>
<!--Below;A button.Upon clicking the button a JS function named myFunc() is executed and hence changing the color of the text above.-->
   <button type="button" onclick="myFunc()"> Change Color </button>
<!--Below;JS Script.Created a function.Go to the doc,then get Element By the assigned I'd,then go to style,then go to style type,then change it as commanded.-->
   <script>
      function myFunc() {
         document.getElementById("jstyle").style.color = "green";
         document.getElementById("jstyle").style.fontWeight = "bold";
         document.getElementById("jstyle").style.fontSize = "300%";
      }
   </script>
</body>
</html>
